    "strings": [
      "CONFIDENTIAL",
      "Steel City Insurance Group",
      "Patricia Nowak, Senior Broker",
      "03/15/2026",
      "RE: Keystone Commercial Builders, Inc. \u2014 Transfer Submission",
      "300 Liberty Avenue, Suite 1200, Pittsburgh, PA, 15222",
      "To: Underwriting Department, Hallmark Insurance Group",
      "Dear Underwriting Team,",
      "Account Overview",
      "We are pleased to submit ",
      "Keystone Commercial Builders, Inc.",
      " for your review and consideration. The insured is a general",
      "contracting for commercial and institutional construction \u2014 healthcare facilities, educational buildings, and corporate offices",
      "throughout Western Pennsylvania, headquartered in Pittsburgh, with approximately 42 years of operating history. Coverage is",
      "requested for Workers' Compensation, General Liability, Commercial Auto, Commercial Property.",
      "Coverage Requested",
      "Workers' Compensation:",
      " Workers' Compensation coverage is requested for approximately 425 employees across all",
      "operations.",
      "General Liability:",
      " General Liability coverage is requested on an occurrence form with $2,000,000.00 per occurrence and",
      "$4,000,000.00 aggregate, including standard premises/operations and products/completed operations.",
      "Commercial Auto:",
      " Commercial Auto coverage for 15 vehicles including hired and non-owned auto.",
      "Commercial Property:",
      " Commercial Property coverage for all scheduled locations on a special form with replacement cost",
      "valuation.",
      "Loss History Summary",
      "The claims history warrants review; management has implemented corrective measures to address identified exposures. Over",
      "the review period, the insured has incurred ",
      "52",
      " total claims with ",
      "$1,315,756.27",
      " in total paid losses and ",
      "$1,489,697.06",
      " total",
      "incurred. Currently, ",
      "12",
      " claims remain open and ",
      "40",
      " have been closed.",
      "Annualized loss ratio is ",
      "18.7%",
      " (avg annual incurred $297,939.41 against current annual premium $1,589,164.70 over 5 loss",
      "years).",
      "Breakdown by coverage line:",
      "\u2022 ",
      " 35 claims, $1,126,509.19 paid, $1,176,100.41 incurred",
      " 8 claims, $105,420.70 paid, $176,946.61 incurred",
      " 8 claims, $47,076.38 paid, $99,900.04 incurred",
      " 1 claim, $36,750.00 paid, $36,750.00 incurred",
      "Note: account experienced a cancellation in ",
      "2022-2023",
      " with Zurich Insurance Group. Reason: Carrier non-renewed \u2014 book of",
      "business exit.",
      "Risk Highlights",
      "\u2022 The insured has implemented a formal return-to-work program that has reduced lost-time claims by over 30%.",
      "\u2022 The insured maintains a dedicated safety committee that meets monthly and conducts quarterly site audits.",
      "\u2022 Management has invested significantly in employee safety training, with all field personnel OSHA-certified.",
      "\u2022 The insured maintains a formal business continuity and disaster recovery plan tested annually.",
      "\u2022 The organization has achieved ISO 9001 certification, reflecting a commitment to quality and process control.",
      "\u2022 The insured carries contractual risk transfer provisions in all subcontractor and vendor agreements.",
      "\u2022 Background checks and MVR reviews are conducted annually for all employees in safety-sensitive positions.",
      "\u2022 With 425 employees and a structured HR program, the insured maintains low turnover and consistent safety training.",
      "\u2022 42 years of continuous operations under consistent management demonstrates operational stability.",
      "Broker Recommendation",
      "This is a quality account with strong operational controls and we are confident it will perform well in your portfolio.",
      "Please do not hesitate to contact us with any questions or if additional information is required.",
      "Respectfully submitted,",
      "Patricia Nowak",
      "Senior Broker",
      "Page 1 of 2",
      "Page 2 of 2"
    ],
